      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm looking at some digitized census records from Frederick County, Virginia, around 1780. There's a really strange dip in the recorded population density in certain districts compared to the 1770 estimates, even though the local tax records suggest more activity. Any idea what might cause such a sharp, localized fluctuation in a frontier setting like that?",
